What caused the sell-off?

Well, consider this highly speculative, but here goes: One proprietary trader
at a major bank tells my colleague Steven Sears that “basket trading” at
Citigroup (C), meaning, the trading of groups of stocks that investors
structure on their own to resemble indices, caused the decline.

Speculation is that a trader wanted to sell $1 million notional of stocks and
instead entered $1 billion notional — a typo, in effect — and that that
triggered a sell-off in some stocks and some stocks traded to zero, such as
Accenture (ACN).

Steven has calls in to Citi but has received no comment yet.

A fund manager at a major money management house relates in an email this
afternoon that “Procter [& Gamble (PG)] and Accenture stocks had the huge hit.
Have heard massive program error by Citi. One of those trades where there were
likely three extra zeros added.”
