From:nianic00
I always thought the idea of the euro was rather stupid. You had a bunch of
countries that willingly let go of their power to print money through their
central banks. When you give up that power for a shared central bank,
monetizing your country's debt becomes extremely difficult, as Greece is now
finding out. The EU should have just been a free trade zone.

Anyway, this is going to be a mess. We're not just dealing with Greece here.
Check out this post by Robert Wenzel

http://www.economicpolicyjournal.com/2010/02/beware-july.html

In addition, what about the US? No way we're making the interest payments
without significantly higher taxes and/or massive inflation.

