oil/gas partnerships have historically done). Given market turmoil of last
year, I'm not so tolerant of seeing unexpected cuts in the distribution now.

TTO - Tortoise Capital Resources - "invests primarily in privately-held and
micro-cap public companies". This is inherently risky itself, because of the
lack of transparency and the resultant TTO management "guess" of TTO's nav
summary for private firms. So my recently established position has been very
small indeed with TTO. (whew!)

Not too thrilled that management would be so overly invested in a problem
company that they would jeopardize TTO's distribution.
Makes me wonder if Tortoise's TPZ, TYN also have management problems that I
should be concerned about. (I hold decent positions in these two Tortoise
funds.)

